<div id="review_351899099" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/351899099" />
    <a title="Nia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8531261-nia"><img alt="Nia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1334006784p2/8531261.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/351899099?book_show_action=true">Jun 19, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nia" href="/user/show/8531261-nia">Nia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer351899099" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer740226397462184407">Slave is a book centered solely on the post traumatic fear experienced by a slave and how her new Master tries to help her deal with the trauma. There are no sex scenes, BDSM scenes (aside from traumatic memories), or even erotic scenes. The closest you will come to erotica are a few kisses. <br/><br/>With that said, I found the book to be well developed and the story interesting. The entire book is about helping Brianna (Anna) deal with making her own choices and seeing the world in a different light. Ve</span>
  <span id="freeText740226397462184407" style="display:none">Slave is a book centered solely on the post traumatic fear experienced by a slave and how her new Master tries to help her deal with the trauma. There are no sex scenes, BDSM scenes (aside from traumatic memories), or even erotic scenes. The closest you will come to erotica are a few kisses. <br /><br />With that said, I found the book to be well developed and the story interesting. The entire book is about helping Brianna (Anna) deal with making her own choices and seeing the world in a different light. Very serious, deep and emotional read about the effects of sadistic non-consensual slavery and how a man takes it upon himself to try to heal her and show her true trust.<br /> </span>
  <a data-text-id="740226397462184407" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
